nt color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umistressoftherose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistress of the Rose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Black Rose</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/28/02 3:20:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   This is All I have to say</span><hr size=1> I have not been to the boards in a long time and if I get banned for saying this it will be no loss to me. /semi-rant on<br>
<br>
I came to Firiona Vie server as a chance to roleplay.  I had been on a server in a roleplay guild that was not as roleplaying as I wanted it to be, albeit they did do better than most.  I came here with a background for my character and I have learned much.  I, one of the biggest bashers of F&amp;F next to Bane of course, now actually speak to quite a few of them ooc.  I have changed much and even came here often.  I remember being idealistic and I have finally reached a happy medium.  I try to roleplay as much as I can but do recognize that TRAIN TO ZONE is a viable option whenever I have 20 frogs chasing me in lguk.  With that background I will now begin and see if this turns to a rant.<br>
<br>
I met Shintou when I was simply a level 9 enchantress in WC.  Firiona Vie came down and I was trying to roleplay the position of being a spy and Shintou and I had plenty of fun roleplaying.  Now I have roleplayed and talked to him the rest of the server from him being in House Sel'Quar to League of Shadows to Fist of Hate so on.  He was a marvelous roleplayer.  He spoke his mind freely and that is what got him into so many messes with people who hide behind roleplaying as an excuse to powergame.  I admire him for the will to keep coming to this board with so much that was going on. I chose simply to ignore it as there was no point in me coming here ... if there was anyone I wanted to speak to I could do so in game either IC or OOC.  I didn't need someone like Ankles moderating it.  Ankles I don't know you outside of the board but really from what I have seen here you aren't that bad of a PERSON.  But I will say you are horrible at being a moderator.  <br>
<br>
/cry Shintou<br>
If you read this and restart as an unknown let me know who you are.  Maybe I can tutor your new character like I tried to tutor the old one.  You were one of the few on this server that care about roleplaying and You WILL be missed by those of us that cared for you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 321<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/28/02 7:33:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I'd like to rebut the horrible moderator part</span><hr size=1> A horrible moderator deletes opinions that don't agree or even bans people that don't agree with him.  An example of this would the the old &quot;Q&quot; from the EQ monk board.  Ankles snapped and vented.  She didn't abuse moderation powers to support her opinion.  She just spoke her mind.  The worst moderation act I've seen here was Val's moving Coinfists post -- basically a mild surprise at that and nothing more.  Hardly horrible.  I've seen horrible.  This is really pretty good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/28/02 7:44:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'd like to rebut the horrible moderator part</span><hr size=1> Agreed. If a moderator says their opinion, it's abuse. Well, I suppose if a white person hits a person of another race, it's immediatly an act of hate. <br>
<br>
And it seems agreeing with people is kissing their asses. Oh no, I guess I'm a &quot;Moderator's Pet&quot; :P.Grow up already, really. There's not too much to be earned by &quot;kissing up&quot; to people who control threads on a specific message board. <br>
<br>
I'm not afraid to oppose Jaxy, Ankles, Valquiss, or Fritz. They respect people's opinions. Tiesto, on the other hand, I am. He'll rip out my throat and make me eat my words, but that's why I admire him :P Note, the four moderators/admins I listed were the only ones I've really noticed, I've probably forgot a couple. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/28/02 8:53:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'd like to rebut the horrible moderator part</span><hr size=1> I didn't see Ankles do anything wrong. <br>
<br>
All she said was one single short sentence telling Shintou that he was helping to ruin the very forum that he loved. <br>
<br>
She never told him to shut up. <br>
<br>
She did not demand an ultimatum from him. <br>
<br>
She did not modify his posts. <br>
<br>
She did not delete his post. <br>
<br>
She spoke her opinion on a sub-form (Soapbox) that is reserved for strong opinions. <br>
<br>
The only reason that some people are blaming this on Ankles is because Shintou is a well-loved and highly-respected role player that.....ahem.... lost his composure, his feelings got hurt, and he had a hissy fit. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
