<br>
As for moderators giving their opinion ... that's not moderation and if you are going to do so you need to state before hand this is not moderation or anything having to do with my post at all IF you even do it at all.  It's just one of those times when you are supposed to set the example.  I was here from nearly the beginning of the server and I stayed as long as it was small.  When it got a bit larger, as one of my friends told me, it might have just gotten to the mods heads a bit.  They were virtual celebrities.  I'm not saying people are horrible just saying their moderation isn't the best.  When moderating you must stick to your own rules when you break them you are no longer setting an example and people won't give a rats ass about the board ... I believe a good number of people had left the board. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaldnor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaldnor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 4:34:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hmm</span><hr size=1> Hmm..<br>
<br>
This can indeed go on forever friends. Why is it that ye keep speaking of things that cannot be undone? Does it help? I think not. Does it get worse? It might and I belive it will.<br>
<br>
I personally did not know this Shintou character but from what I have read about him he seems like a very good roleplayer that tends to whine a bit to much. I should not say to much since I do perhaps not know as much of this as I should.<br>
<br>
Whining, my friends, does not help. That goes for both sides.<br>
